message: the correct setting is 'socialauth_complete' but readthedocs.org has the incorrect value  http://django-social-auth.readthedocs.org/en/latest/configuration.html

and for some reason the master branch in github also has the incorrect value https://github.com/omab/django-social-auth/blob/master/doc/configuration.rst   but  the pypi site has the correct value:  http://pypi.python.org/pypi/django-social-auth/
if you have the incorrect value, you will see this error message: Reverse for 'complete' with arguments '(u'facebook',)' and keyword arguments '{}' not found.
wow!  fixed 4 minutes after the bug is reported --  omab is super-responsive!!  Thanks!!
